<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911210-0090</DOCNO><DOCID>911210-0090.</DOCID><HL>   International Brief -- Fanuc Ltd.:   Capital Investment Plans   Are Scaled Back for 1992</HL><DATE>12/10/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   J.FAN</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>FACTORY EQUIPMENT (FAC)</IN><RE>FAR EAST (FE)JAPAN (JA)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)</RE><LP>   Machinery maker Fanuc Ltd., Tokyo, has slated only 10billion yen ($78.1 million) for capital investment in thenext fiscal year, less than half the 26 billion yen thecompany expects to spend in the fiscal year ending March 31,1992.   Next year's spending will be funneled into research andmeasures to increase efficiency, but not into expansion ofthe company's production base, a Fanuc spokesman said. Amongprojects to be put on hold is an injection machinery factorythat Fanuc had originally planned to build next year. &quot;Thatplan is postponed indefinitely,&quot; the spokesman said.</LP><TEXT>   Because of a slump in the Japanese machinery and robotmarket, Fanuc also has scaled back its capital investmentplan for the current fiscal year. Last year at this time, thecompany had expected to invest a total of 36 billion yenduring the period. However, that figure has been pared downto the latest estimate of 26 billion yen.</TEXT></DOC>